<tr><td bgcolor="#3F403F" width="98%" class="cheader"><table cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 border=0 width=100%><TR><td><font class="h1font">Articles</td><form method='post' action=''><input type="hidden" name="PHPSESSID" value="178dc98989d669ff4092283ae3e60f13" /><td align='right' valign='bottom'><select name='select' onChange='go(this)'><option selected>More DeckTech Articles</option><option value='#'> </option><option value='/starwarsccg/articles/index.php3'>Star Wars: CCG</option><option value='/vs/articles/index.php'>Marvel VS</option><option value='/heroclix/articles/articles.php'>HeroClix</option><option value='/lotr/articles/articles.php'>Lord of the Rings</option><option value='/magic/articles/articles.php'>Video Games and Movies</option><option value='/wars/articles/articles.php'>Wizards Minis</option></select></td></form></tr></table></td><td bgcolor="3F403F" valign="top" align="right" width="22"><img src="/starwarsccg/gfx/theme1/topcorner.gif" width="23" height="22" border="0" vspace="0" hspace="0" align="right"></td></tr>
<tr><td width="98%" colspan=2><table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="5" class="cbody">
<tr><td><font class="h1font"> Grading the Erratas 6/12/06<br></font><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Overall Rating:</b> </font><img src="/starwarsccg/gfx/theme1/star.gif" width="19" height="18" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/starwarsccg/gfx/theme1/star.gif" width="19" height="18" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/starwarsccg/gfx/theme1/star.gif" width="19" height="18" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/starwarsccg/gfx/theme1/star.gif" width="19" height="18" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/starwarsccg/gfx/theme1/star.gif" width="19" height="18" border="0" align="absmiddle"><font size='1'>(4.90)</font><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Author:</b> <A HREF='http://www.decktech.net/starwarsccg/main/mpage.php?member=2349'>Michael "Pistone" Pistone</A></font><font class="afont"> <a href='http://www.decktech.net/starwarsccg/main/mpage.php?member=2349&sub=1'> (Subscribe to this member)</a><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Date Submitted:</b> June 12, 2006</font><p align='justify'><font class="bfont"> So a new batch of erratas came out today.  If you are unfamiliar with them please read them here before reviewing this article, so you have a better idea of what I am talking about.  http://www.swccgpc.com/modules.php?name=News&file=article&sid=11<br />
<br />
Before the list here is a brief idea of my grading.  An A is a card that is still very useful but not as abusive.  A B is a card that needed to be fixed and has very limited uses.  A C is a card that needed to be fixed, but now is basically unplayable.  A D would be a card that needed to be fixed and now is equally as bad.  An F would be a card that needed to be fixed and is now worse than it was originally.<br />
<br />
1. (V) Security Precautions:<br />
<br />
What&#39;s out: Cannot start this using (V) Readiness, cannot deploy it to a site you do not occupy to get around Goo, you must first play a character and then the effect.  Slows things slightly.<br />
<br />
Everything else remains the same and I think this errata was very well done.  Deploying the effect to get around Goo Nee Tay for your first character always seemed a bit unnecessary because there was a card (V) Molator that could effectively do that well already.  Additionally, you cannot start this in a (V) Combat Readiness deck.  Good, because the last thing this game needed was a way to have a guaranteed 2 BONUS force on turn 1.<br />
<br />
Question: If it cannot deploy on a non-battleground, why does it need the &quot;If this site is a non-battleground...place this efect in Used pile&quot; wording?  Seems you could cut this down some.<br />
<br />
Grade: A<br />
<br />
2. (V) Encampment:<br />
<br />
What&#39;s out: Cannot start this using (V) Planning.<br />
<br />
A similar result happens for the LS as the (V) Precautions errata only to a lesser degree.  While (V) Precautions is the significantly stronger card, I assume that it will still see play even with the errata&#39;d form, while (V) Encampment will not.  The concept of cheaper deployment during the first few turns of the game was significantly bad however, and led to the rapid increase in the speed of the game.  Good to slow things back down some.<br />
<br />
Grade: C+<br />
<br />
3. (V) Combat Readiness/(V) Careful Planning:<br />
<br />
What&#39;s out: The &quot;bounce&quot;.  You cannot start two 2/1 locations, so you are limited to at most 5 force of your own starting.  You also only get to start 3 effects.<br />
<br />
This puts these cards on a more even level with previous objectives.  They still create new decktypes which is great for variety in the game, while not making old objectives obsolete entirely.  Also, the dreaded &quot;bounce&quot; is gone thank GOD.  This will allow both players to play their decks and get to start things the way they want.  GOOD.  <br />
<br />
However, I wonder why we still need the overly powerful used function of these cards.  A used interrupt that plays to the top of reserve deck seems like something that wasn&#39;t needed for these already powerful cards.  That dumbs down the game and discourages tracking.<br />
<br />
Grade: B<br />
<br />
4. (V) Jabba the Hutt<br />
<br />
What&#39;s out: Uploading scum more than once.  Doubling power of ALL aliens at the site (effectively eliminating the Jabba/Elis beats strategy).  The +2 for movement text.<br />
<br />
This removes the current version of Scum from the environment but I think many players view that as a welcome change.  He is still likely the best Jabba for a scum deck and retains lots of strong qualities for both use of a fortress and in uploading scum.  When the meta slows down after the redux do not be surprised to see him in a much more tamed down version of scum.<br />
<br />
Question: Besides reducing length, why was the +2 for movement text removed?<br />
<br />
Grade: B+<br />
<br />
5. (V) Inconsequential Losses/(V) Superficial Damage<br />
<br />
What&#39;s out: Timer mines.<br />
<br />
Good, timer mines were gay.  That&#39;s all I have to say about this.<br />
<br />
Grade: A+<br />
<br />
6. (V) Sim Aloo<br />
<br />
What&#39;s out: All of his gametext.<br />
What&#39;s in: All new gametext.<br />
<br />
Well clearly Sim had been overpowered and abusive in decks.  So it is good that his gametext was completely changed, and in fact I was in favor with removing all of it.  Free Elis, Cease Fire, Barrier and WMAOP were all a bit much to deal with.  However, I have no clue who would use this character now with his rather useless gametext.  It is possible the non (V) Sim Aloo is better now.<br />
<br />
Grade: C<br />
<br />
7. (V) Green Squadron 1<br />
<br />
What&#39;s out: +2 for / and /<br />
What&#39;s in: Diversionary Tactics??<br />
<br />
I honestly don&#39;t even know what Diversionary Tactics does, but if you use it then hooray for you.  I think since the +2 / and / text was removed this card is now effectively useless but removed a bad strategy from the game.  I think the ship should at least have some immunity to attrition to be playable nowadays.<br />
<br />
Grade: C<br />
<br />
<br />
So how does this affect the meta?  Well for the time being we have even fewer DS options than we had a week ago, but this is certainly a step in the right direction.<br />
<br />
So Overall<br />
<br />
Affect on the Meta Grade: D (The meta is going to be horrible until the redux.)<br />
<br />
Future of the game grade: B+ (There is a light at the end of the tunnel).<br />
<br />
Hope you enjoyed the article.<br />
<br />
-Michael Pistone<br />
Quinnipiac University &#39;07 Economics and Mathematics<br />
